reviews.review: There is so much to critisize about the movie but what sticks out the most is that they give this character, after years of misery and lonneliness finally a moment filled with happiness just to kill them of in the next few seconds and for what? Nothing really. I thought these movies were supposed to be about hope yet the ending was incredibly depressing.

There are two different levels to consider. The perception on the sequel trilogy in total and the perception of the Rise of Skywalker itself. 

The sequel trilogy is completely flawed by not having a masterplan in advance and the contradicting directions JJ Abrams and Rian Johnson took. 

If I look at the Rise of Skywalker as a rsult of the mess before, its actually pretty good solved to bring everything to an end and to bring all the pieces of the puzzle together. But as a single movie its to stuffed with revelations, story pieces and character devolepment is happening on such a speed that many actions are not plausible.
It has to achieve what Last Jedi should have done and does a lot of reconning. 

JJ Abrams does what he had to do, but is it a masterpiece? Definetely NO!
In total the whole sequel trilogy is pointless and we end up at the same point as we have been at the end of Return of the Jedi.

tRoS provides an unoriginal, uncreative and ultimately just plain boring end to a trilogy of unoriginal and uncreative films, and happily sends of any character development for a 2hr fuckfest of Macguffin after Macguffin, and pointless character after pointless character, ending in a climax that proves just how much the new trilogy lacked any personality and creativity

Last Jedi hurt the story they try it to salvage it creating a mediocre movie with plot holes and inconsistencies and a fan service check list make sequels look like masterpieces The sequels have their shortcomings but at least they were original  and tried things
Absolutely unoriginal, breaks all star wars lore. Completely incoherent.
Still a good film its difficult to live up to episode 6 due to new ideas being further difficult to come up with still a good film just not amazing.
Inconsistent, hurried, indecisive and confusing, "Rise of Skywalker" sins in every way. The best thing about this movie is that it's over.
A copy of chapter XI, without imagination, without attention and full of clich√©s.  It was not worth the entrance.
The film had some good cinematography but the story had no sense of build or momentum.Predictable and uninspiring, audience did get a sense of closure to the whole saga though which was good.
